The Impostors Genesis Aliens represent the foundational NFT collection of the Impostors ecosystem, and serve as passes the Impostors Genesis Season which will play host to seven unique events. Only 10,420 of these intergalactic creatures will ever exist! Each Genesis Character has a combination of over 200 traits and will provide stat-based advantages in various metaverse game modes.

Impostors is a social gaming metaverse that bridges the gap between today’s Twitch culture and the future of immersive metaverses. The game is built in Unreal Engine and the team consists of over 30 world-class engineers and builders with experience working at AAA studios including Epic Games, Roblox, Pixar, and more. Impostors brings a breath of fresh air into the gaming and crypto world by creating a social gaming metaverse that is truly player-owned and powered.

Su D. Oku Saves Earth! is an NFT Collection of 25,000 increasingly difficult sudoku puzzles separated into volumes and chapters.

Saga 1! - 40 volumes: Easy

Saga 2! - 40 volumes: Medium

Saga 3! - 40 volumes: Hard

#SAGA 5! - 5 VOLUMES: EXTREME!


Each difficulty is distinguished by a unique background pattern, and the answer keys and instructions on how to play can be found hosted [here](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1PWKFsqmDxMdK6WZ8GTwXha_DHg7eor5P?usp=sharing)!

Each Volume follows our hero, Su D. Oku as he criss-crosses time, space, the world and even the galaxy to save planet Earth. 

But this is not just a story, with each NFT, 90% of royalties and initial sales go towards fusion research like [ITER](https://www.iter.org/) and [Wendelstein 7-X](https://www.ipp.mpg.de/w7x), which is helping to save the planet from a climate change crisis through fusion energy. The same type of energy that powers the Sun! Help Su D. Oku Save Earth. Today!

assets.description:
How do colors affect us?
 the effect of colors works on three levels . The first is the subjective - which is, the personal meaning we put on colors according to the experiences we have gone through or the beliefs we have developed.
The second level is cultural, and it is related to the symbolism that is rooted in the environment and society in which we live.
The third level, is the universal.
Years ago it became clear that different colors have different effects on the human brain. Some can raise the level of alertness and concentration, others can upset, and there are also colors that really affect blood pressure and even appetite and metabolism. These effects are cross-cultural and affect all human beings in a similar way, and yet most of us are not fully aware of them.
